  "text": "The rule of thumb in multivariate Cox regression models is that the events per variable (EPV) must be at least 10 to produce a reliable model [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, a recent study demonstrates that an EPV of 5-10 gives similar reliability to an EPV ≥10 [CITATION_3] . Therefore in our study with 32 events, a prediction model may contain 3-6 variables.",
